&lt;h1 id="laundry"&gt;Laundry&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Version 1.0&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;October 2004&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As E. B. White said, &amp;ldquo;good writing is rewriting.&amp;rdquo; I didn&amp;rsquo;t realize this when I was in school. In writing, as in math and science, they only show you the finished product. You don&amp;rsquo;t see all the false starts. This gives students a misleading view of how things get made.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>